        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:48PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Logansport, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Logansport, Walton, Lincoln, Onward, Clymers, Deacon, New Waverly,
Anoka, and Adamsboro.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
